</i></p><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-20_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Revalidation is a regulatory requirement for healthcare professionals in the UK, designed to affirm their competence, promote lifelong learning, and enhance patient care. For professionals like nurses, doctors, dental staff, and allied health professionals, revalidation is essential to their professional journey. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the intricacies of revalidation, key facts, statistics, and recommended best practices.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-ad7c" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-22_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-23_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Patient safety and quality care</strong> - Revalidation aims to ensure that healthcare professionals remain fit to practise, thereby enhancing patient safety and the quality of care.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular intervals</strong> - Most healthcare professionals must revalidate every 3-5 years, depending on their profession.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-32_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulatory bodies </strong>- Key regulatory bodies include the General Medical Council (GMC), Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC), Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC), and General Dental Council (GDC).
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-35_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-36_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Revalidation</strong> - A process by which healthcare professionals demonstrate that they remain up to date and fit to practise.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Continuing Professional Development (CPD)</strong> - Ongoing education and training activities that professionals undertake to maintain and enhance their skills.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Appraisal</strong> - A systematic review of an individual's performance, often involving feedback from colleagues and patients.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3">Importance of revalidation
</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Revalidation is crucial for several reasons:


<br>
















































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-51_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Maintaining standards</strong> - Ensures that healthcare professionals adhere to the latest standards and practices.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Public confidence</strong> - Enhances trust in the healthcare system by ensuring professionals are competent and up to date.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>Professional development</strong> - Encourages continuous learning and professional growth.

</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-58_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-59_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-60_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for revalidation implementation</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>For nurses (NMC)</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-64_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>CPD requirements</strong> - Nurses must complete 35 hours of CPD, with 20 hours being participatory.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Practice hours </strong>- Evidence of 450 practice hours over three years is required.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-69_ pf-text-1"><strong>Reflective accounts</strong> - Five reflective accounts on CPD activities and practice-related feedback.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-71_ pf-text-1"><strong>Confirmation</strong> - A third party, usually a senior nurse or line manager, must confirm the nurse's revalidation evidence.

</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>For doctors (GMC)</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-75_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-76_ pf-text-1"><strong>Annual appraisals</strong> - Doctors must undergo annual appraisals based on the GMC's Good Medical Practice framework.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-78_ pf-text-1"><strong>CPD activities</strong> - Engagement in CPD activities relevant to their scope of practice.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-80_ pf-text-1"><strong>Feedback and reflection</strong> - Incorporating feedback from patients and colleagues and reflecting on their practice.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-82_ pf-text-1"><strong>Supporting information</strong> - Evidence of quality improvement activities, significant events, and personal development plans.


</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-84_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>For dental professionals (GDC)</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-86_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>CPD cycle </strong>- Dental professionals must complete 100 hours of CPD over a five-year cycle.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-89_ pf-text-1"><strong>Mixed learning </strong>- CPD activities must include a mix of general and verifiable CPD.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-91_ pf-text-1"><strong>Annual declaration</strong> - An annual statement confirming CPD compliance must be submitted to the GDC.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-93_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>For Allied Health Professionals (HCPC)</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-95_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-96_ pf-text-1"><strong>CPD standards</strong> - Meeting the HCPC's five CPD standards, including keeping a record of CPD activities and demonstrating their impact on practice.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-98_ pf-text-1"><strong>Portfolio submission</strong> - Submission of a CPD portfolio if selected for audit.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-100_ pf-text-1"><strong>Reflection </strong>- Reflecting on how CPD activities improve their practice and benefit service users.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-102_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-103_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-104_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations for healthcare organisations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-106_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-107_ pf-text-1"><strong>Structured support</strong> - Provide structured support and resources to assist healthcare professionals with their revalidation.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-109_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and development</strong> - Offer access to training and development opportunities through accredited platforms like ComplyPlus™.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-111_ pf-text-1"><strong>Feedback mechanisms</strong> - Establish robust mechanisms for collecting and acting on feedback from patients and colleagues.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-113_ pf-text-1"><strong>Documentation</strong> - Maintain comprehensive documentation to support revalidation evidence.
